(Description)
Given n pairs of parentheses, write a function to generate all combinations of well-formed parentheses.

--- Soltuion ---
class Solution {
    List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();

    public List<String> generateParenthesis(int n) {
        cases(result, new StringBuilder(), n*2, n, n);

        return result;
    }

    private void cases(List<String> result, StringBuilder sb, int max, int open, int close) {
        if (sb.length() == max) {
            result.add(sb.toString());
        }
        else {
            if (open == close) {
                sb.append("(");
                cases(result, sb, max, open-1, close);
                sb.setLength(sb.length() - 1);
            }
            else {
                if (open > 0) {
                    sb.append("(");
                    cases(result, sb, max, open-1, close);
                    sb.setLength(sb.length() - 1);
                }

                if (close > 0) {
                    sb.append(")");
                    cases(result, sb, max, open, close-1);
                    sb.setLength(sb.length() - 1);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

--- Approach ---
The key concept was tracking open parentheses & close parentheses.
Given number n, open & close parentheses must be n times.
Therefore I append "(" or ")" to the StringBuilder followed by the rule.
- "(" should begin to form the well-formed parentheses. => When (open == close) algorithm must append "(" at first.
- Then, when (open < close) well-formed parentheses have two options.
    1. Appending another "("
    2. Appending ")" to close current open parenthese.
- To cover those cases, algorithmn called recursion at the both cases.

  And, finally, StringBuilder delete added parenthese after recursion to share clean Sb.
